        "summary": {
          "diffs": [
            {
              "file": "bench-artifacts/cache-api.md",
              "patch": "Index: bench-artifacts/cache-api.md\n===================================================================\n--- bench-artifacts/cache-api.md\t\n+++ bench-artifacts/cache-api.md\t\n@@ -0,0 +1,48 @@\n+# Cache API\n+\n+A simple key-value cache implementation using a Map.\n+\n+## createCache()\n+\n+Creates and returns a cache instance with get, set, delete, and clear methods.\n+\n+```js\n+import { createCache } from './cache.mjs'\n+\n+const cache = createCache()\n+```\n+\n+## Methods\n+\n+### get(key)\n+\n+Retrieves a value by key from the cache. Returns the cached value if it exists, otherwise `undefined`.\n+\n+```js\n+const value = cache.get('my-key')\n+```\n+\n+### set(key, value)\n+\n+Stores a value in the cache with the given key. Returns the value that was set.\n+\n+```js\n+cache.set('my-key', 'my-value')\n+const returned = cache.get('my-key') // 'my-value'\n+```\n+\n+### delete(key)\n+\n+Removes a value from the cache by key. Returns the result of `Map.prototype.delete()`.\n+\n+```js\n+cache.delete('my-key')\n+```\n+\n+### clear()\n+\n+Removes all entries from the cache.\n+\n+```js\n+cache.clear()\n+```\n",
              "additions": 48,
              "deletions": 0,
              "status": "added"
            }
          ]
        },
